      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "URL rewriting",
      "pos": [
        21115,
        21128
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following except from a Web.config file in the root of a Cloud Services hosted application demonstrates how to perform URL rewriting when using the CDN.",
      "pos": [
        21129,
        21285
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Requests from the CDN for content it will cache are redirected to specific folders within the application root based on the type of the resource (such as scripts and images).",
      "pos": [
        21286,
        21460
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The addition of the rewrite rules performs the following redirections:",
      "pos": [
        22614,
        22684
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The first rule allows you to embed a version in the file name of a resource, which is then ignored.",
      "pos": [
        22690,
        22789
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Filename_v123.jpg<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is rewritten as <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Filename.jpg<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.",
